It is the 51st combination of the sexagenary cycle, following {{ill|Mizunoto-ushi|ja|癸丑|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} and preceding {{ill|Kinoe-usagi|ja|乙卯|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. In {{ill|Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|ja|陰陽五行思想|1=Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, the {{ill|Heavenly Stem|ja|十干|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} '''Kinoe''' (甲) represents Yang {{ill|Wood|ja|木|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, and the {{ill|Earthly Branch|ja|十二支|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} '''Tora''' (寅) also represents Yang Wood, forming a {{ill|Harmonious Combination|ja|五行思想#比和（ひわ）|比和|1=Wuxing (Chinese philosophy)#Harmonious Relationship (比和)|2=ja|3=五行思想#比和（ひわ）|lt=Harmonious Relationship (Five Elements)|4=el|5=Ου Σιν|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}.
== Kinoe-tora Years == After the Common Era, a year is a Kinoe-tora year if, when divided by 60, the remainder is 54.
