=== Events === * [[:en:Kaei|Kaei]] 7 / [[:en:Ansei|Ansei]] 1 (1854) - {{ill|Tora no Taihen|ja|寅の大変|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tora no Taihen|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tora no Taihen|qq=}} - [[:en:1854 Tōkai earthquake|Ansei Tōkai earthquake]], [[:en:1854 Nankai earthquake|Ansei Nankai earthquake]]<ref>[https://cir.nii.ac.jp/crid/1390572174727612416 Tsuchi Yasunobu, CiNii] Tsuchi Yasunobu (ed.): "Historical Records of Earthquakes and Tsunamis in Kōchi Prefecture," Disaster Science and Technology Research Materials 57, i-253, 1981-03-20, National Research Institute for Earth Science and Disaster Resilience.</ref> ==Months of Yang Wood Tiger== == Kinoe-tora Months == In years where the last digit of the Western calendar is 3 or 8 (corresponding to the [[:en:Heavenly Stems|Heavenly Stems]] of Mizunoto (癸) or Tsuchinoe (戊)), the first month of the year is a Kinoe-tora month. However, this applies to the {{ill|Lunisolar calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Lunisolar calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Lunisolar calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}} or [[:en:Solar term|Solar term]] (from [[:en:Lichun|Risshun]] to the day before [[:en:Jingzhe|Keichitsu]]). ==Days of Yang Wood Tiger== == Kinoe-tora Days == === Selected Days === Kinoe-tora days are the second day of {{ill|Hassō|ja|八専|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hassō|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hassō|qq=}} (excluding intercalary days). == See Also == * {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|Sexagenary cycle comprehensive|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sexagenary cycle|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sexagenary cycle|qq=}} * [[:en:Heavenly Stems|Heavenly Stems]] * [[:en:Earthly Branches|Earthly Branches]]
